			<ns0:name>s...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/108394971971967673680/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">The browser plugin does two sorts of relative path resolutions: one for src resolution relative to the page, and one for nexe resolution relative to the manifest URL.  Both need more comprehensive tests, especially

1) with src= in the embed tag
2) plugin.src= dynamically
3) setAttribute('src', ...)

These tests need to be used

a) with and without &amp;lt;base&amp;gt; tags
b) with relative and absolute URLs
c) with manifests as data URIs
